cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper proposes a computer vision system based on deep learning for algae monitoring, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed system can be installed on robotic platforms such as USVs and UAVs, indicating that it also falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning for algae detection implies that it could also be classified under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper involves image processing and pattern recognition, which are relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning for real-time detection suggests that it could also be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
